This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the task of few-shot segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of deep learning techniques for prototype refinement also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of adaptation and fusion techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of neural networks for few-shot segmentation also suggests that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) category. Finally, the use of datasets such as PASAL-$5^i$ and COCO-$20^i$ suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
